article.headline: Fairfield 77, Siena 66
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- DeWitt Maxwell had 18 points and three other Fairfield players scored in double figures to lead the Stags over Siena 77-66 Wednesday night. Terrence Todd had 16 points, Deng Gai 14 and Michael Bell 12 for the Stags (7-7, 4-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Fairfield built on a 33-31 halftime lead, making it 54-39 in the second half before Siena responded with a 14-3 run. But the Saints (3-11/1-3) couldn't get any closer than 57-53. Jack McClinton scored a career-high 23 points for Siena, while Michael Haddix had 16 points and nine rebounds. David Ryan added 13 rebounds.
